or-row\">\n				<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a9ece84 elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column\" data-id=\"a9ece84\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n			<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap  elementor-element-populated\">\n					<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n				<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-674cb65 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"674cb65\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n				<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n					<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\"><p>A<b> </b>major WordPress release is on the way,<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and with it, you will be getting tons of new features and functionality to enhance your experience. This major release is being called </span><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/news/2020/07/wordpress-5-5-beta-1/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b>WordPress 5.5</b></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and it is scheduled to be released on August 11, 2020.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this blog post, we’re going to give you an in-depth idea of all the new features and improvements that will be coming with WordPress 5.5 so you can prepare yourself early on for this major update. </span></p></div>\n				</div>\n				</div>\n						</div>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n						</div>\n			</div>\n		</section>\n				<section data-particle_enable=\"false\" data-particle-mobile-disabled=\"false\" class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7e48596 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default elementor-section elementor-top-section\" data-id=\"7e48596\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n						<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n				<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n				<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-50fd829 elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column\" data-id=\"50fd829\" data-element_type=\