(18, 1, '2020-08-04 06:22:37', '2020-08-04 06:22:37', '<h2>about</h2>\n5th Studio is a unique spatial design agency, working across the fields of architecture, urban design, infrastructure and landscape. We work with our clients and commissioners to create beauty and enduring value from complex situations.\n\nWe apply our spatial intelligence to a broad spectrum — from delivering buildings through to research and strategy. We strive to be visionary, innovative and persuasive, and in all our projects we commit to successful outcomes beyond the traditional role of a designer: leading the team, transforming risk into opportunity, raising profile and clearly articulating the objectives of a project.\n\n5th Studio offers bespoke services, tailored to the particular needs of clients and projects — we are a rigorous, can-do organisation ready to take on any challenge.\n<h2>the people</h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li data-filter=\"*\">All</li>\n 	<li data-filter=\".eael-cf-director\">Director</li>\n 	<li data-filter=\".eael-cf-associate\">Associate</li>\n 	<li data-filter=\".eael-cf-architect\">Architect</li>\n 	<li data-filter=\".eael-cf-designer\">Designer</li>\n</ul>\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/1.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/1.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Tom Holbrook</h5>\nProfessor Tom Holbrook came to architecture tangentially, co-founding 5th Studio in 1997 as a spatial design agency, working across the fields of architecture, urban design, infrastructure and landscape.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Oliver Smith</h5>\nOliver co-founded 5th Studio in 1997 along with Tom Holbrook. He leads the practice’s exploration of cutting edge approaches to sustainability, materiality and construction.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>February Phillips</h5>\nFebruary’s wide-ranging experience includes working as a lead consultant, project architect, project manager and contract administrator on multi-award winning projects, varying in contract value from £40 thousand to £20 million.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/4.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/4.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Beth Lambert</h5>\nBeth is an Associate and experienced Project Architect with varied practical knowledge across the fields of urban design and architecture.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Liz King</h5>\nLiz is an experienced, qualified architect and a key member of the 5th Studio team as an associate. Her experience spans arts, residential, commercial and educational building sectors, both in terms of planning and delivery stages.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/6.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/6.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Kieran Perkins</h5>\nKieran is an associate at 5th Studio, a qualified architect and an experienced urban &amp; landscape designer. Kieran works between the Cambridge and London studios and has been involved with the practice for more than decade.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/7.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/7.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>John Cain</h5>\nAs an associate John brings an attentive oversight to the projects he leads, bringing his impeccable sense of detail and consideration to projects at all scales, and is a key member of the London studio.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/10.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/10.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Anastasia Orphanidou</h5>\nSince joining 5th Studio Anastasia played a major role in the development of 5th Studio’s analysis of the plans for the strategic growth of Oxford-Milton Keynes-Cambridge Corridor: Future Planning Options Project, commissioned by the National Infrastructure Commission.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/11.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/11.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Raluca Cirstoc</h5>\nRaluca is an architect whose work inhabits the political and social spectrum of architecture and urban design.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/12.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/12.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Iona Foster</h5>\nIona has been instrumental in developing 5th Studio’s presence in Oxford, leading to the opening of our studio there in 2019. In all her work she brings experience of working on a variety of public building projects in the arts and education sectors.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/11-1.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/11-1.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Tom Brownill</h5>\nTom is an experienced architectural designer, who has worked across a number of different sectors within the practice, from masterplanning and strategy to construction.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/12-1.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/12-1.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Sam Clayton</h5>\nSam is a Senior Designer at 5th Studio. Sam enjoys a hands-on design process, assisting the practice across several projects ranging from strategic masterplanning in Chester, detailed design for reworking heritage buildings and construction.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/13.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/13.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Dan Miodrag</h5>\nDan is an experienced designer, skilled in developing architectural and public realm proposals across a range of scales and complexities, from transport interchanges to furniture scale interventions.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/14.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/14.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Helena Jordan</h5>\nHelena is an experienced designer who has worked across a range of sectors, from master-planning and strategic infrastructure to public realm proposals.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/15.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/15.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Piotr Kruk</h5>\nPiotr is a designer with experience across large scale urban design, strategy, public engagement and meanwhile projects.\n\n<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/16.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/16.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n<h5>Conor Moses</h5>\nConor is a designer with experience working across a variety of scales from urban strategy through to detail testing. Since joining 5thStudio, Conor has worked on a wide range of projects throughout London.', 'About', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about', '', '', '2020-08-06 09:57:07', '2020-08-06 09:57:07', '', 0, 'http://localhost/sh-arms/?page_id=18', 0, 'page', '', 0),
