(214, 1, '2020-08-05 15:11:00', '2020-08-05 15:11:00', '<h2>about</h2>		\n		<p>5th Studio is a unique spatial design agency, working across the fields of architecture, urban design, infrastructure and landscape. We work with our clients and commissioners to create beauty and enduring value from complex situations.</p><p>We apply our spatial intelligence to a broad spectrum — from delivering buildings through to research and strategy. We strive to be visionary, innovative and persuasive, and in all our projects we commit to successful outcomes beyond the traditional role of a designer: leading the team, transforming risk into opportunity, raising profile and clearly articulating the objectives of a project.</p><p>5th Studio offers bespoke services, tailored to the particular needs of clients and projects — we are a rigorous, can-do organisation ready to take on any challenge.</p>		\n			<h2>the people</h2>		\n				<ul>\n											<li data-filter=\"*\">All</li>\n											<li data-filter=\".eael-cf-director\">Director</li>\n											<li data-filter=\".eael-cf-associate\">Associate</li>\n											<li data-filter=\".eael-cf-architect\">Architect</li>\n											<li data-filter=\".eael-cf-designer\">Designer</li>\n									</ul>\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/1.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/1.jpg\" alt=\"\"><h5>Tom Holbrook</h5><p>Professor Tom Holbrook came to architecture tangentially, co-founding 5th Studio in 1997 as a spatial design agency, working across the fields of architecture, urban design, infrastructure and landscape.</p>\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2.jpg\" alt=\"\"><h5>Oliver Smith</h5><p>Oliver co-founded 5th Studio in 1997 along with Tom Holbrook. He leads the practice’s exploration of cutting edge approaches to sustainability, materiality and construction.</p>\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3.jpg\" alt=\"\"><h5>February Phillips</h5><p>February’s wide-ranging experience includes working as a lead consultant, project architect, project manager and contract administrator on multi-award winning projects, varying in contract value from £40 thousand to £20 million.</p>\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/4.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/4.jpg\" alt=\"\"><h5>Beth Lambert</h5><p>Beth is an Associate and experienced Project Architect with varied practical knowledge across the fields of urban design and architecture.</p>\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5.jpg\" alt=\"\"><h5>Liz King</h5><p>Liz is an experienced, qualified architect and a key member of the 5th Studio team as an associate. Her experience spans arts, residential, commercial and educational building sectors, both in terms of planning and delivery stages.</p>\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/6.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/6.jpg\" alt=\"\"><h5>Kieran Perkins</h5><p>Kieran is an associate at 5th Studio, a qualified architect and an experienced urban &amp; landscape designer. Kieran works between the Cambridge and London studios and has been involved with the practice for more than decade.</p>\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/7.jpg\" data-lazy-src=\"http://localhost/sh-arms/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/7.jpg\" alt=\"\"><h5>John Cain</h5><p>As an associate John brings an attentive oversight to the projects he leads, bringing his impeccable sense of detail and consideration to projects at all scales, and is a key member of the London studio.</p>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-08-05 15:11:00', '2020-08-05 15:11:00', '', 18, 'http://localhost/sh-arms/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
